# Apps Web → Apps Docs (Diátaxis)

Any **new or materially changed** user-facing behavior in `apps/web` (routes, flows, config, **public HTTP API** under `apps/web/src/app/api/`, billing gates, AI features, auth) needs **matching updates** in `apps/docs` in the same change set. Do not merge web-only surface area without documentation.

## Diátaxis — use the right doc type

| Quadrant | Purpose | When to add or extend |
|----------|---------|------------------------|
| **Tutorials** | Learning-oriented, step-by-step; first success path | New developer or user onboarding, end-to-end “do this once” lessons |
| **How-to guides** | Task-oriented recipes; assumes basics | “How to …” for a concrete goal (auth pattern, import, deploy checklist) |
| **Reference** | Information-oriented technical map | **API**: methods/paths, parameters, bodies, response envelope, status codes, error shapes; also stable factual lists (CLI flags, env vars) |
| **Explanation** | Understanding-oriented context and “why” | Architecture, trade-offs, data model concepts, security or billing model (not step lists) |

**Do not** put tutorial steps inside reference pages, or tables of endpoints inside explanation-only essays. Cross-link between quadrants instead.

## Layout (`apps/docs`)

- MDX lives under `apps/docs/content/`. Register pages in `apps/docs/content/_meta.ts` so the sidebar stays accurate.
- Prefer clear **separation by quadrant** in paths or titles, for example:
  - `content/tutorials/…` — tutorials
  - `content/how-to/…` — how-to guides
  - `content/reference/…` — reference (e.g. REST API under `apps/web/src/app/api/`)
  - `content/explanation/…` or existing top-level conceptual pages (e.g. `architecture.mdx`) — explanation
- **Reference** for HTTP APIs must document: route, method(s), auth, query/body fields, success `{ data }` / error `{ error }` envelope, relevant status codes, and pagination/CORS behavior where applicable (align with `.cursor/rules/public-api.mdc`).

## Rules

- If you touch `apps/web/src/app/api/**`, add or update **Reference** in `apps/docs` for every affected route.
- If you add a user-visible feature or change behavior, add or update the smallest set of **Tutorial / How-to / Explanation** pages that keep Diátaxis boundaries honest.
- Keep intro/overview copy honest about what is shipped; avoid “placeholder” language once the feature exists.
